 fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Blore was born in 1155, in Staffordshire, England. He married F Blore in 1180, in Eastham, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1200, in Audley, Staffordshire, England, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1155–1200":"1155–1200","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1181–1287":"1181–1287","1200":"1200","1155":"1155","1287":"1287","1181":"1181","1180":"1180","Audley, Staffordshire, England":"Audley, Staffordshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Eastham, Cheshire, England":"Eastham, Cheshire, England","Eastham, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Eastham, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1155–1200":"1155–1200","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1181–1287":"1181–1287","1200":"1200","1155":"1155","1287":"1287","1181":"1181","1180":"1180","Audley, Staffordshire, England":"Audley, Staffordshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Eastham, Cheshire, England":"Eastham, Cheshire, England","Eastham, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Eastham, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1155–1200":"1155–1200","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1181–1287":"1181–1287","1200":"1200","1155":"1155","1287":"1287","1181":"1181","1180":"1180","Audley, Staffordshire, England":"Audley, Staffordshire, Angleterre","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, Angleterre","Eastham, Cheshire, England":"Eastham, Cheshire, Angleterre","Eastham, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Eastham, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Blore est né en 1155,